text: Haberdashers' Aske's School for Girls is a private school for girls in Elstree, Hertfordshire. It was started in 1875 by the Worshipful Company of Haberdashers. In 2013 100% of GCSEs were A*-C and 69.8% were A*.https://www.habsgirls.org.uk/sub_page.php?agegroup=sixth_form&area;=results_destinations&page;_id=3§ion;_id=8 ==References== Category:1875 establishments in England Category:Schools in Hertfordshire Category:British public schools
